write an http/1.0 web server that serves static files from the specified directory
>start by handling one request at a time
>support the GET and HEAD verbs
>then if you’ve got time, choose from the list:
    threaded/evented request handling;
    serve index.html if the directory is requested;
    return the correct MIME type based on the filename’s extension;
    implement ERB (that’s the `<% some ruby code %>` thing).
